1
00:00:22,623 --> 00:00:26,459
<i>(Chibi‐Usa)</i>
<i>I heard that Mamo has been</i>
<i>starting to see a young and</i>
<i>beautiful widow.</i>

2
00:00:26,492 --> 00:00:28,261
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>What!? A widow!?</i>

3
00:00:28,294 --> 00:00:30,263
<i>(Chibi‐Usa)</i>
<i>I know Usagi's clumsy and</i>
<i>annoying...</i>

4
00:00:30,296 --> 00:00:31,264
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Chibi‐Usa!</i>

5
00:00:31,297 --> 00:00:32,966
<i>(Chibi‐Usa)</i>
<i>But cheating is still wrong!</i>

6
00:00:33,166 --> 00:00:36,937
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>That's true. Wait! The bad guys</i>
<i>are after the widow's beautiful</i>
<i>memories!</i>

7
00:00:36,970 --> 00:00:40,974
In the name of the Moon
we'll punish you!

8
00:00:52,318 --> 00:01:02,335
♪

9
00:01:02,335 --> 00:01:22,422
♪

10
00:01:22,422 --> 00:01:42,442
♪

11
00:01:42,442 --> 00:02:02,468
♪

12
00:02:02,468 --> 00:02:10,476
♪

13
00:02:26,326 --> 00:02:28,595
Oh, hey, Mamoru!

14
00:02:28,629 --> 00:02:29,495
[gasp]

15
00:02:29,563 --> 00:02:31,131
Sorry for the trouble!

16
00:02:31,164 --> 00:02:33,600
Oh, not at all! I
enjoyed coming over.

17
00:02:33,634 --> 00:02:35,335
[gasp]

18
00:02:35,401 --> 00:02:37,571
Just give me a call
if you need me.

19
00:02:37,604 --> 00:02:40,173
Will do! Need a ride?

20
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:42,609
Oh, don't worry about it.
I can get back on my own.

21
00:02:42,643 --> 00:02:44,444
It is part of the
job, after all.

22
00:02:44,477 --> 00:02:45,345
See ya!

23
00:02:45,411 --> 00:02:46,780
What's going on here?

24
00:02:46,813 --> 00:02:48,314
Hey, Ami, what's up?

25
00:02:48,348 --> 00:02:50,116
Don't play dumb, Mamoru!

26
00:02:50,150 --> 00:02:52,018
That key...!

27
00:02:52,085 --> 00:02:53,587
[gasp]

28
00:02:53,620 --> 00:02:57,624
As Usagi's best friend, I can't
just sit back and ignore what I
saw happen!

29
00:02:57,658 --> 00:02:58,959
Huh?

30
00:02:58,992 --> 00:03:00,701
Uhhh...

31
00:03:04,304 --> 00:03:08,474
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Drive to the Heavens: The Dream</i>
<i>Car Fueled with Love</i>

32
00:03:26,993 --> 00:03:29,663
...and done!

33
00:03:29,663 --> 00:03:31,565
How ya doin' down there?

34
00:03:31,632 --> 00:03:33,834
Great! I'm all finished.

35
00:03:33,867 --> 00:03:36,169
Not too much more to go!

36
00:03:36,169 --> 00:03:37,671
Why don't we take a break?

37
00:03:37,704 --> 00:03:39,339
Sure!

38
00:03:39,339 --> 00:03:41,007
Wow, so it's true!

39
00:03:41,041 --> 00:03:42,676
This is out of
character for her.

40
00:03:42,676 --> 00:03:45,679
Ami? Working part time at
an auto repair shop?

41
00:03:45,679 --> 00:03:47,247
I can't believe it.

42
00:03:47,313 --> 00:03:52,352
[nervous gasps]

43
00:03:52,385 --> 00:03:53,720
[sighs of relief]

44
00:03:53,754 --> 00:03:56,823
You know, it doesn't look like
she's being forced to work
here...

45
00:03:56,857 --> 00:04:00,026
What if she's been
brainwashed or something?!

46
00:04:00,060 --> 00:04:02,102
<i>(Mamoru)</i>
<i>Usako?</i>

47
00:04:02,168 --> 00:04:02,703
[gasp]

48
00:04:02,703 --> 00:04:04,104
Huh?

49
00:04:04,170 --> 00:04:06,372
What are you and the other
girls doing here?

50
00:04:06,372 --> 00:04:07,774
Hi, Mamo!

51
00:04:07,841 --> 00:04:10,544
Usagi! They're falling...
they're falling...!

52
00:04:10,577 --> 00:04:13,947
<i>[screaming]</i>

53
00:04:14,014 --> 00:04:16,683
What are you all doing here?!

54
00:04:16,717 --> 00:04:18,719
Ami, do you know them?

55
00:04:18,719 --> 00:04:25,626
[coughing]

56
00:04:25,692 --> 00:04:30,631
Hold on a second, Mamoru's been
cheating on Usagi!?

57
00:04:30,697 --> 00:04:32,432
[spitting]

58
00:04:32,465 --> 00:04:35,602
Uh, I did not cheat.

59
00:04:35,635 --> 00:04:36,235
...Right?

60
00:04:36,235 --> 00:04:38,772
[giggle]

61
00:04:38,805 --> 00:04:40,473
Hey! What's going on!?

62
00:04:40,541 --> 00:04:45,311
I know that Usagi is
clumsy and possessive, but
cheating is still wrong!

63
00:04:45,378 --> 00:04:46,913
Who's side are you even on!?

64
00:04:46,980 --> 00:04:50,383
Wow, Mamoru, you're the last
person I thought would cheat on
their girlfriend!

65
00:04:50,416 --> 00:04:52,819
Men are just total
pigs, aren't they!

66
00:04:52,886 --> 00:04:53,654
Mhm!

67
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:55,221
Ugh, come on!

68
00:04:55,255 --> 00:04:59,125
No, you've got it all wrong!
At first I thought he was
cheating, too, but

69
00:04:59,159 --> 00:05:03,670
Natsumi is just a mechanic who
owns this repair shop and was
helping him out.

70
00:05:03,737 --> 00:05:05,305
Seriously?

71
00:05:05,338 --> 00:05:08,408
<i>(Mamoru)</i>
<i>Yeah! It's really simple...</i>

72
00:05:08,441 --> 00:05:13,346
<i>See, what happened was I asked</i>
<i>Natsumi to fix my car, so she</i>
<i>came over to deliver it.</i>

73
00:05:13,413 --> 00:05:15,616
<i>That's all!</i>

74
00:05:15,616 --> 00:05:18,685
[chuckle]

75
00:05:18,752 --> 00:05:23,123
So, then I guess the
keys that Ami saw...

76
00:05:23,123 --> 00:05:24,791
They were just
your car keys.

77
00:05:24,791 --> 00:05:26,492
I'm sorry...

78
00:05:26,527 --> 00:05:30,831
Well, duh! There's no way that
Mamo would ever even think of
cheating on me!

79
00:05:30,864 --> 00:05:34,134
Weren't you the one doubting him
up until a few minutes ago?

80
00:05:34,134 --> 00:05:36,803
Shut up! Stop trying
to cause trouble!

81
00:05:36,837 --> 00:05:40,674
[sticking tongue out]

82
00:05:40,707 --> 00:05:45,378
Oh, by the way, Natsumi, how's
that car you've been working on?

83
00:05:45,445 --> 00:05:46,847
It's almost done, isn't it?

84
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:48,715
Mhm!

85
00:05:48,782 --> 00:05:50,851
This car's my dream!

86
00:05:50,884 --> 00:05:54,387
<i>Once it's finished, I'm going to</i>
<i>drive it all around town!</i>

87
00:05:54,454 --> 00:05:58,959
Of course, having you around,
Ami, has really helped!

88
00:05:58,992 --> 00:06:01,635
I never would have gotten this
far without your assistance.

89
00:06:01,668 --> 00:06:06,507
Oh, no, you had already
done most of the hard work
before I even got here.

90
00:06:06,507 --> 00:06:08,008
Give yourself more credit!

91
00:06:08,008 --> 00:06:12,012
I mean, you were able to catch
onto basic mechanics pretty
quickly!

92
00:06:12,045 --> 00:06:14,681
And you even fixed some
stuff without my help!

93
00:06:14,681 --> 00:06:17,818
It's almost like you can
understand how the car feels.

94
00:06:17,851 --> 00:06:20,420
You really have a
talent for this!

95
00:06:20,486 --> 00:06:21,354
That's our Ami!

96
00:06:21,387 --> 00:06:23,423
Way to go, girl genius!

97
00:06:23,489 --> 00:06:24,858
Doesn't surprise me at all!

98
00:06:24,858 --> 00:06:25,759
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Woo‐hoo!</i>

99
00:06:25,826 --> 00:06:28,428
All right, ready to put in
some more work?

100
00:06:28,494 --> 00:06:30,697
<i>(Ami)</i>
<i>Yeah!</i>

101
00:06:43,710 --> 00:06:46,279
[sigh]

102
00:06:46,346 --> 00:06:48,048
<i>(Tiger's Eye)</i>
<i>Who's that?</i>

103
00:06:48,048 --> 00:06:48,549
Hm?

104
00:06:48,582 --> 00:06:50,216
Another older woman?

105
00:06:50,250 --> 00:06:55,689
Ew, and she's a grease monkey,
huh? I mean, if that's what
you're into...

106
00:06:55,722 --> 00:07:00,567
[laughing]

107
00:07:00,601 --> 00:07:01,902
You okay?

108
00:07:01,902 --> 00:07:05,438
All right, let me explain
it to both of you.

109
00:07:05,471 --> 00:07:10,544
This one is a woman who has
reached the peak of all other
older women.

110
00:07:10,577 --> 00:07:13,146
So, she's a grandmother?

111
00:07:13,213 --> 00:07:16,149
[groan]

112
00:07:16,216 --> 00:07:17,951
Shut up and listen!

113
00:07:18,018 --> 00:07:23,256
If she were a fish, this woman
would be the fattiest of tuna,
or, the best filet of sole!

114
00:07:23,289 --> 00:07:25,491
Ya get it? She's a widow!

115
00:07:25,559 --> 00:07:27,961
Mmm.. not interested.

116
00:07:27,994 --> 00:07:35,301
Well then, unfortunately it
seems that a jewel is but a rock
to those who don't realize it's
value.

117
00:07:35,335 --> 00:07:38,438
Anyway, I'll be
taking this target.

118
00:07:38,471 --> 00:07:49,315
[tinkering ]

119
00:07:49,349 --> 00:07:51,451
Tomokazu...

120
00:07:59,693 --> 00:08:01,294
What is that?

121
00:08:01,294 --> 00:08:05,706
Nice, huh? The two of us are
gonna fix this beauty up and
make it drivable again!

122
00:08:05,772 --> 00:08:07,974
Are you kidding?
That'll take forever!

123
00:08:08,008 --> 00:08:11,311
Come on, we can do it
if we work together!

124
00:08:11,311 --> 00:08:12,478
Huh?

125
00:08:12,513 --> 00:08:15,882
We're gonna turn our little shop
into the garage of dreams!

126
00:08:15,949 --> 00:08:19,553
We'll be able to repair any car
and be the best auto shop in the
world!

127
00:08:27,828 --> 00:08:29,495
[sigh]

128
00:08:29,530 --> 00:08:30,831
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>A widow!?</i>

129
00:08:30,864 --> 00:08:35,235
Yeah, Natsumi and her husband
opened that repair shop together

130
00:08:35,301 --> 00:08:38,905
But unfortunately he passed away
suddenly about three years ago.

131
00:08:38,972 --> 00:08:41,742
It's really heartbreaking,
especially because before he

132
00:08:41,808 --> 00:08:45,846
passed they had promised each
other that they would rebuild
that vintage car together.

133
00:08:45,879 --> 00:08:49,182
I see. That must be why
she's so attached to it.

134
00:08:49,215 --> 00:08:52,152
Don't overwork yourself, okay?
|

135
00:08:52,185 --> 00:08:55,689
You're not planning to stay
there and help her with that car
forever, are you, Ami?

136
00:08:55,689 --> 00:09:00,861
But if I quit before it's
finished, what was the point
in helping her at all?

137
00:09:00,894 --> 00:09:05,371
Natsumi has been running that
garage alone since Tomokazu
died.

138
00:09:05,405 --> 00:09:07,340
So she needs an extra hand!

139
00:09:07,373 --> 00:09:11,878
And besides, I can tell
that that car is filled
with their love, so

140
00:09:11,912 --> 00:09:14,715
getting it to run is something
I'd really like to see.

141
00:09:14,715 --> 00:09:16,517
Hm.

142
00:09:16,550 --> 00:09:19,520
Oh, Ami...

143
00:09:19,553 --> 00:09:21,287
[small gasp]

144
00:09:23,557 --> 00:09:25,258
<i>(Chibi‐Usa)</i>
<i>Hey, Pegasus?</i>

145
00:09:25,291 --> 00:09:28,795
I thought Ami's dream was to
become a doctor...

146
00:09:28,862 --> 00:09:32,733
So why do you think she decided
to help out at that garage?

147
00:09:32,766 --> 00:09:35,936
I'm afraid I don't know.

148
00:09:35,969 --> 00:09:39,039
But, people are allowed to
have more than one dream...

149
00:09:39,072 --> 00:09:40,240
Huh?

150
00:09:40,273 --> 00:09:43,577
Some people wish to make
dreams come true for others.

151
00:09:43,577 --> 00:09:45,812
Whoa, honestly?

152
00:09:45,879 --> 00:09:49,650
Will I be able to have
a dream like that?

153
00:09:49,716 --> 00:09:51,051
Of course you will.

154
00:10:06,106 --> 00:10:06,406
[tires screeching]

155
00:10:09,776 --> 00:10:13,446
<i>(Hawk's Eye)</i>
<i>Excuse me, I'm having</i>
<i>problems with my engine...</i>

156
00:10:13,514 --> 00:10:14,781
<i>...Mind taking a look?</i>

157
00:10:14,848 --> 00:10:16,683
Sure thing.

158
00:10:23,023 --> 00:10:24,090
[gasp]

159
00:10:26,059 --> 00:10:28,061
Tomokazu...

160
00:10:28,061 --> 00:10:29,229
Huh!?

161
00:10:29,229 --> 00:10:33,266
<i>[evil laugh] She completely</i>
<i>fell for my disguise!</i>

162
00:10:33,299 --> 00:10:35,869
<i>Making her mine should be easy!</i>

163
00:10:35,902 --> 00:10:39,205
[gasp] [sigh]

164
00:10:39,239 --> 00:10:41,908
Natsumi!

165
00:10:52,452 --> 00:10:56,890
<i>(Ami)</i>
<i>According to what the doctor</i>
<i>said, Natsumi is suffering from</i>
<i>severe exhaustion.</i>

166
00:10:56,923 --> 00:11:01,568
Oh, wow. She must have been
working long hours all alone.

167
00:11:01,602 --> 00:11:04,805
Well, she won't be able to
work again for a while.

168
00:11:04,838 --> 00:11:06,472
But, the car...

169
00:11:07,941 --> 00:11:09,843
[sad sigh]

170
00:11:13,113 --> 00:11:16,116
What's wrong with me?
Tomokazu's gone...

171
00:11:16,116 --> 00:11:18,484
There's no way he'd
show up like that.

172
00:11:21,321 --> 00:11:22,989
Don't grieve, Natsumi.

173
00:11:23,023 --> 00:11:25,158
[gasp] It's you!

174
00:11:41,608 --> 00:11:50,617
<i>♪Sailor Moon</i>

175
00:11:53,887 --> 00:12:03,870
<i>♪Sailor Moon</i>

176
00:12:05,806 --> 00:12:10,310
I lost my parents when I was
very young. I've been so lonely
without them.

177
00:12:10,343 --> 00:12:15,582
Since then, I've been searching
for a woman to share my sadness
with.

178
00:12:15,649 --> 00:12:18,018
That's when I found you!

179
00:12:21,922 --> 00:12:23,389
[gasp]

180
00:12:23,423 --> 00:12:27,227
I promise that you won't have to
live in sadness any longer.

181
00:12:27,260 --> 00:12:29,429
<i>(Hawk's Eye)</i>
<i>Please, sell that repair</i>
<i>shop of yours...</i>

182
00:12:29,495 --> 00:12:30,496
[gasp]

183
00:12:30,531 --> 00:12:33,667
And let's go on a trip
together, right now!

184
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:36,036
[gasp]

185
00:12:38,872 --> 00:12:39,940
No!

186
00:12:40,006 --> 00:12:42,709
Dammit. Interrupted.

187
00:12:42,743 --> 00:12:46,713
I thought fixing that
car was your dream!

188
00:12:46,713 --> 00:12:51,552
If you just give up on it before
you finish, everyone will be
really disappointed!

189
00:12:51,552 --> 00:12:54,287
Everyone? What
do you mean?

190
00:12:54,354 --> 00:12:56,923
Wait a minute!
Who let you in?

191
00:12:56,957 --> 00:13:00,901
I was seducing... uh, I mean,
talking about our future!

192
00:13:00,934 --> 00:13:02,135
Back off, ascot!

193
00:13:02,202 --> 00:13:04,571
Natsumi, you can't
give up on your shop!

194
00:13:04,605 --> 00:13:07,974
Everyone is over there
doing their best to
help you right now!

195
00:13:08,041 --> 00:13:09,409
[groan]

196
00:13:09,409 --> 00:13:11,945
Hey! Natsumi, what
are you doing!? Wait!

197
00:13:11,978 --> 00:13:13,246
I have a favor to ask you.

198
00:13:13,246 --> 00:13:14,748
Huh?

199
00:13:23,256 --> 00:13:26,760
(Makoto)
Ami, I'm supposed to turn
this clockwise, right?

200
00:13:26,760 --> 00:13:28,128
(Ami)
Uh‐huh!

201
00:13:28,161 --> 00:13:32,265
(Usagi)
I'm just gonna cut this wire and
get it out of my way, cool?

202
00:13:32,265 --> 00:13:35,101
(Ami)
Usagi, calm down!
Don't hit that so hard!

203
00:13:35,135 --> 00:13:37,270
(Usagi)
Nervous giggle

204
00:13:37,270 --> 00:13:38,905
<i>(Rei)</i>
<i>Way to break the</i>
<i>car, Usagi...</i>

205
00:13:38,939 --> 00:13:40,106
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>No one asked you, Rei!</i>

206
00:13:40,140 --> 00:13:41,808
Ami...

207
00:13:41,842 --> 00:13:46,279
See, everyone wants the car to
run, so they're all doing their
best to make it work!

208
00:13:46,312 --> 00:13:47,581
Huh?

209
00:13:47,614 --> 00:13:51,151
Making that car run, it's not
just your dream now...

210
00:13:51,184 --> 00:13:53,286
...it's everyone's dream!

211
00:13:53,286 --> 00:13:58,091
[all chattering]

212
00:13:58,124 --> 00:14:00,160
[happy sigh]

213
00:14:00,994 --> 00:14:02,803
<i>(Hawk's Eye)</i>
<i>Is that what this is all about?</i>

214
00:14:02,803 --> 00:14:08,642
Why would you even need to fix
that clunker when I have my
super cool sports car right here

215
00:14:08,642 --> 00:14:10,476
Let's get going now.

216
00:14:10,476 --> 00:14:11,311
I'm sorry...

217
00:14:11,311 --> 00:14:12,345
[gasp]

218
00:14:12,378 --> 00:14:15,481
Look, I don't think I can
go with you after all.

219
00:14:15,481 --> 00:14:20,621
You see, this garage
may be small, but it's
full of big dreams.

220
00:14:20,654 --> 00:14:22,322
I'm staying here.

221
00:14:22,355 --> 00:14:24,525
[happy sigh]

222
00:14:24,558 --> 00:14:26,326
It wasn't a request...

223
00:14:26,326 --> 00:14:27,293
[gasp]

224
00:14:27,327 --> 00:14:28,662
<i>(Natsumi)</i>
<i>[screaming]</i>

225
00:14:28,695 --> 00:14:29,630
Huh?

226
00:14:29,663 --> 00:14:31,064
(Natsumi)
Someone, help!

227
00:14:31,131 --> 00:14:32,833
He, he kidnapped her!

228
00:14:32,866 --> 00:14:34,635
Come on!

229
00:14:34,668 --> 00:14:35,502
Oww...

230
00:14:38,071 --> 00:14:39,506
Get in!

231
00:14:44,310 --> 00:14:46,179
[screaming]

232
00:14:47,748 --> 00:14:50,651
Damn! They don't
give up, do they?

233
00:14:57,691 --> 00:14:59,259
[grunt]

234
00:14:59,993 --> 00:15:02,335
[screaming]

235
00:15:02,368 --> 00:15:04,571
Stop it! Don't
be so reckless!

236
00:15:04,605 --> 00:15:08,542
Are you afraid I'll wreck the
car? Like I give a damn...!

237
00:15:08,542 --> 00:15:10,711
[gasp]
What'd you say?

238
00:15:10,744 --> 00:15:13,446
I knew it! You're
nothing like Tomokazu!

239
00:15:13,514 --> 00:15:17,283
you're the type who doesn't
understand cars at all!

240
00:15:17,350 --> 00:15:18,685
[tires screeching]

241
00:15:18,719 --> 00:15:22,589
I'm only interested
in your dreams, honey!

242
00:15:22,623 --> 00:15:23,690
[gasp]

243
00:15:23,724 --> 00:15:26,860
[running breaths]

244
00:15:26,893 --> 00:15:27,728
[finger snap]

245
00:15:27,728 --> 00:15:28,895
[yell]

246
00:15:30,430 --> 00:15:31,231
[fearful gasp]

247
00:15:31,231 --> 00:15:32,298
[finger snap]

248
00:15:35,569 --> 00:15:36,603
[gasp]

249
00:15:36,637 --> 00:15:38,939
Now, those big dreams of
yours... let's see them!

250
00:15:38,972 --> 00:15:39,873
[gasp]

251
00:15:39,906 --> 00:15:42,142
One...

252
00:15:42,208 --> 00:15:45,111
Two...

253
00:15:45,145 --> 00:15:45,779
...and three!

254
00:15:45,812 --> 00:15:49,983
[screaming]

255
00:15:50,050 --> 00:15:51,918
[fainting sigh]

256
00:15:52,953 --> 00:15:54,254
It's him!

257
00:15:54,287 --> 00:15:55,121
Let's go!

258
00:15:56,222 --> 00:16:01,668
Mercury Star Power Make Up!

259
00:16:17,117 --> 00:16:23,189
<i>(Usagi & Chibi‐Usa)</i>
<i>Moon Crisis Make Up!</i>

260
00:16:53,486 --> 00:16:55,522
<i>(Sailor Mercury)</i>
<i>Hold it right there!</i>

261
00:16:55,556 --> 00:16:56,790
[gasp]

262
00:16:56,823 --> 00:16:58,959
I'm not going to let
you get away with this!

263
00:16:58,992 --> 00:16:59,626
What the‐‐??

264
00:16:59,660 --> 00:17:00,834
<i>(Sailor Moon)</i>
<i>Exactly!</i>

265
00:17:02,468 --> 00:17:06,339
You violated several traffic
laws, and even worse, Natsumi's
precious memories!

266
00:17:06,372 --> 00:17:08,008
We're the pretty guardians...

267
00:17:08,008 --> 00:17:10,977
...who fight for love
and for justice!

268
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:16,316
I am Sailor Moon!

269
00:17:16,349 --> 00:17:19,853
And I am Sailor Chibi‐Moon!

270
00:17:19,853 --> 00:17:23,657
In the name of the Moon,
we'll punish you!

271
00:17:27,060 --> 00:17:31,197
Shine Aqua Illusion!

272
00:17:31,197 --> 00:17:32,733
[evil laugh]

273
00:17:32,766 --> 00:17:34,400
[blowing]

274
00:17:37,403 --> 00:17:38,438
[gasp]

275
00:17:38,505 --> 00:17:41,074
I don't have time to
play with you girls!

276
00:17:41,107 --> 00:17:52,052
Come forth, my Lemures, Ms.
Buranko the Flying Trapeze
Artist Without a harness!

277
00:17:52,052 --> 00:17:57,357
Swinging when there's
no wind... Bura Bura!

278
00:17:57,958 --> 00:18:01,034
Miss Buranko, take care
of these little girls.

279
00:18:01,067 --> 00:18:02,402
Bura Bura!

280
00:18:02,402 --> 00:18:05,972
Bura Bura Bura Bura, catch!

281
00:18:06,039 --> 00:18:06,573
[gasp]

282
00:18:06,607 --> 00:18:08,942
What is this?

283
00:18:08,975 --> 00:18:13,980
[screaming]

284
00:18:14,047 --> 00:18:16,883
[whimper]
We're so high up!

285
00:18:19,052 --> 00:18:21,087
That's not good.

286
00:18:21,087 --> 00:18:23,423
Bura Bura Bura Bura!

287
00:18:23,423 --> 00:18:25,759
Ahhh help!

288
00:18:25,759 --> 00:18:27,928
Nice catch, Sailor Mercury!

289
00:18:27,928 --> 00:18:29,963
Bura Bura Bura Bura!

290
00:18:29,996 --> 00:18:32,398
Sailor Moon, try to swing!

291
00:18:32,432 --> 00:18:34,067
[grunt]

292
00:18:34,100 --> 00:18:36,069
Mercury!

293
00:18:36,102 --> 00:18:39,305
[screaming]

294
00:18:39,339 --> 00:18:41,141
Bura Bura Bura Bura!

295
00:18:41,174 --> 00:18:42,909
You're heavy...

296
00:18:42,943 --> 00:18:45,411
Chibi‐Moon, whatever
you do, don't let go!

297
00:18:45,612 --> 00:18:48,148
We have to do something,
or we're done for!

298
00:18:48,181 --> 00:18:52,819
So lovely, but no
sign of Pegasus!

299
00:18:52,853 --> 00:18:55,255
Humph!

300
00:18:55,288 --> 00:18:59,660
Enough games, Miss Buranko. Make
sure you get rid of all of them!

301
00:18:59,693 --> 00:19:04,871
Bura Bura Bura Bura!

302
00:19:04,938 --> 00:19:07,608
...Bura!

303
00:19:07,641 --> 00:19:09,275
Ahh!

304
00:19:09,309 --> 00:19:13,514
[screaming]

305
00:19:13,547 --> 00:19:15,148
[Tarzan yell]

306
00:19:15,181 --> 00:19:15,949
[screaming]

307
00:19:15,982 --> 00:19:18,484
Tuxedo Mask, you're here!

308
00:19:18,519 --> 00:19:21,622
Sailor Moon! You'e put on
some weight, haven't you?

309
00:19:21,655 --> 00:19:25,659
[groan] Are you not
seeing those two!?

310
00:19:25,659 --> 00:19:29,630
Oh! Sorry...!

311
00:19:38,872 --> 00:19:40,807
Bura Bura Bura Bura!

312
00:19:40,841 --> 00:19:41,908
Here she comes!

313
00:19:41,975 --> 00:19:43,510
If my calculations
are correct...

314
00:19:43,510 --> 00:19:46,847
Bura Bura Bura Bura..!
Snip! Snip? Snip, snip
snip!?

315
00:19:46,847 --> 00:19:50,884
The law of pendulum
motion saved us!

316
00:19:50,917 --> 00:19:52,085
Now's your chance, you two!

317
00:19:52,152 --> 00:19:53,019
‐Right!
‐Right!

318
00:19:54,187 --> 00:19:58,659
Please, Pegasus, protect
everyone's dream!

319
00:20:02,536 --> 00:20:04,938
Twinkle Yell!

320
00:20:11,044 --> 00:20:12,813
Bura Bura Bura!

321
00:20:13,847 --> 00:20:15,549
[neigh]

322
00:20:25,626 --> 00:20:33,800
Moon Gorgeous Mediation!

323
00:20:46,379 --> 00:20:50,584
Stage out!

324
00:20:59,860 --> 00:21:01,768
Curses! Bested by little girls!

325
00:21:08,875 --> 00:21:11,011
You ready?

326
00:21:11,044 --> 00:21:14,715
Mhm. Here goes!

327
00:21:17,551 --> 00:21:21,054
[engine failing]

328
00:21:24,725 --> 00:21:27,260
<i>Please let it start!</i>

329
00:21:28,261 --> 00:21:30,631
[gasp]
<i>[engine starting]</i>

330
00:21:30,697 --> 00:21:33,767
No way, it works!

331
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:35,368
You did it!

332
00:21:36,537 --> 00:21:39,205
[cheering]

333
00:21:39,239 --> 00:21:41,074
[blast]

334
00:21:41,107 --> 00:21:45,411
[coughing]

335
00:21:45,411 --> 00:21:47,213
[gasps]

336
00:21:48,414 --> 00:21:51,952
Uhh...

337
00:21:51,985 --> 00:21:56,422
[laughing]

338
00:21:56,456 --> 00:21:57,958
Thanks so much, Ami!

339
00:21:57,991 --> 00:22:02,402
I'll keep trying to fix this
car, but next time, I won't be
in such a rush!

340
00:22:02,435 --> 00:22:05,271
I have all the time in
the world, after all!

341
00:22:05,271 --> 00:22:07,340
Natsumi!

342
00:22:09,109 --> 00:22:14,247
[laughter]

343
00:23:52,352 --> 00:24:00,794
<i>I, Small Lady, aka Chibi‐Usa,</i>
<i>have decided to train under</i>
<i>Japan's top swordswoman.</i>

344
00:24:00,861 --> 00:24:04,137
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Wait a minute, that's your</i>
<i>teacher? She's just a kid!</i>

345
00:24:04,204 --> 00:24:06,573
<i>(Chibi‐Usa)</i>
<i>She's really strong and cool!</i>

346
00:24:06,573 --> 00:24:09,409
<i>(Chibi‐Usa)</i>
<i>She left home to go on</i>
<i>a training journey!</i>

347
00:24:09,442 --> 00:24:11,144
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Sounds like she's hiding</i>
<i>something!</i>

348
00:24:11,311 --> 00:24:16,482
<i>Next time on Sailor Moon SuperS,</i>
<i>"Aiming for the Top: The Pretty</i>
<i>Swordswoman's Dilemma."</i>

349
00:24:16,550 --> 00:24:18,451
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>The moonlight is a messenger</i>
<i>of love.</i>

